{"entries":[{"id":"scofield-pro-1-21","title":"Proverbs 1:21","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":1,"verseStart":21,"chapterEnd":1,"verseEnd":21},"content":"<p>ter\" subType=\"x-osis2mod\" n=\"$Rev: 3769 $ (SWORD: 1.9.0)\"/></p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-3-1","title":"Proverbs 3:1","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":3,"verseStart":1,"chapterEnd":3,"verseEnd":1},"content":"<p>The Lord said The general character of the second message to Judah is: (1) of reproach that the example of Jehovah's chastening of the northern kingdom 2 Kings 17:1-18 had produced no effect upon Judah, e.g. Jeremiah 3:6-10. (2) of warning of a like chastisement impending over Judah, e.g. Jeremiah 3:15-17. (3) of touching appeals to return to Jehovah, e.g. Jeremiah 3:12-14. (4) of promises of final national restoration and blessing, e.g. Jeremiah 3:16-18. Israel \"Israel\" and \"Ephraim\": names by which the northern kingdom (the ten tribes) is usually called in the prophets. When by \"Israel\" the whole nation is meant, it will appear from the context.</p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-3-17","title":"Proverbs 3:17–30:24","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":3,"verseStart":17,"chapterEnd":30,"verseEnd":24},"content":"<p><milestone type=\"x-impor</p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-4-5","title":"Proverbs 4:5","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":4,"verseStart":5,"chapterEnd":4,"verseEnd":5},"content":"<p>repent (See Scofield \"Zechariah 8:14\") .</p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-4-8","title":"Proverbs 4:8","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":4,"verseStart":8,"chapterEnd":4,"verseEnd":8},"content":"<p>ter\" subType=\"x-osis2mod\" n=\"$Rev: 3769 $ (SWORD: 1.9.0)\"/></p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-5-intro","title":"Proverbs 5 — Chapter Introduction","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":5,"verseStart":0,"chapterEnd":5,"verseEnd":0},"content":"<p>ter\" subType=\"x-osis2mod\" n=\"$Rev: 3769 $ (SWORD: 1.9.0)\"/></p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-7-intro","title":"Proverbs 7 — Chapter Introduction","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":7,"verseStart":0,"chapterEnd":7,"verseEnd":0},"content":"<p>ter\" subType=\"x-osis2mod\" n=\"$Rev: 3769 $ (SWORD: 1.9.0)\"/></p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-7-7","title":"Proverbs 7:7","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":7,"verseStart":7,"chapterEnd":7,"verseEnd":7},"content":"<p>repented (See Scofield \"Zechariah 8:14\") .</p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-9-intro","title":"Proverbs 9 — Chapter Introduction","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":9,"verseStart":0,"chapterEnd":9,"verseEnd":0},"content":"<p>ter\" subType=\"x-osis2mod\" n=\"$Rev: 3769 $ (SWORD: 1.9.0)\"/></p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-10-1","title":"Proverbs 10:1","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":10,"verseStart":1,"chapterEnd":10,"verseEnd":1},"content":"<p>ter\" subType=\"x-osis2mod\" n=\"$Rev: 3769 $ (SWORD: 1.9.0)\"/></p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-10-16","title":"Proverbs 10:16","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":10,"verseStart":16,"chapterEnd":10,"verseEnd":16},"content":"<p>ter\" subType=\"x-osis2mod\" n=\"$Rev: 3769 $ (SWORD: 1.9.0)\"/></p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-12-3","title":"Proverbs 12:3","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":12,"verseStart":3,"chapterEnd":12,"verseEnd":3},"content":"<p>the Lord said The Remnant, of whom Jeremiah was the representative, are carefully distinguished from the unbelieving mass of the people. The coming captivity, which they must share, for they too have sinned Jeremiah 15:13 though Jehovah's judgment upon the nation, will be but a purifying chastisement to them, and they receive a special promise Jeremiah 15:11. Verses Jeremiah 15:15-18 give the answer of the Remnant to verses Jeremiah 15:11-14. Two things characterize the believing Remnant always-loyal to the word of God, and separation from those who mock at that word Jeremiah 15:16,17 Cf. Revelation 3:8-10.</p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-12-11","title":"Proverbs 12:11","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":12,"verseStart":11,"chapterEnd":12,"verseEnd":11},"content":"<p>ter\" subType=\"x-osis2mod\" n=\"$Rev: 3769 $ (SWORD: 1.9.0)\"/></p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-12-13","title":"Proverbs 12:13","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":12,"verseStart":13,"chapterEnd":12,"verseEnd":13},"content":"<p>saying The sign of the unmarried prophet is interpreted by the context. The whole social life of Judah was about to be disrupted and cease from the land. But note the promises of verses Jeremiah 16:14-16; 17:7,8.</p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-16-16","title":"Proverbs 16:16","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":16,"verseStart":16,"chapterEnd":16,"verseEnd":16},"content":"<p>ter\" subType=\"x-osis2mod\" n=\"$Rev: 3769 $ (SWORD: 1.9.0)\"/></p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-18-13","title":"Proverbs 18:13","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":18,"verseStart":13,"chapterEnd":18,"verseEnd":13},"content":"<p>ter\" subType=\"x-osis2mod\" n=\"$Rev: 3769 $ (SWORD: 1.9.0)\"/></p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-18-18","title":"Proverbs 18:18","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":18,"verseStart":18,"chapterEnd":18,"verseEnd":18},"content":"<p>ter\" subType=\"x-osis2mod\" n=\"$Rev: 3769 $ (SWORD: 1.9.0)\"/></p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-19-13","title":"Proverbs 19:13","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":19,"verseStart":13,"chapterEnd":19,"verseEnd":13},"content":"<p>ter\" subType=\"x-osis2mod\" n=\"$Rev: 3769 $ (SWORD: 1.9.0)\"/></p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-19-15","title":"Proverbs 19:15","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":19,"verseStart":15,"chapterEnd":19,"verseEnd":15},"content":"<p>repent (See Scofield \"Zechariah 8:14\") .</p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-19-20","title":"Proverbs 19:20","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":19,"verseStart":20,"chapterEnd":19,"verseEnd":20},"content":"<p>fear (See Scofield \"Psalms 19:9\") . repented (See Scofield \"Zechariah 8:14\") .</p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-20-15","title":"Proverbs 20:15","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":20,"verseStart":15,"chapterEnd":20,"verseEnd":15},"content":"<p>fifth month i.e. August.</p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-20-28","title":"Proverbs 20:28","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":20,"verseStart":28,"chapterEnd":20,"verseEnd":28},"content":"<p>ter\" subType=\"x-osis2mod\" n=\"$Rev: 3769 $ (SWORD: 1.9.0)\"/></p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-20-30","title":"Proverbs 20:30","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":20,"verseStart":30,"chapterEnd":20,"verseEnd":30},"content":"<p>carried away captives Cf. 2 Kings 24:10-16. The complete captivity of Judah came eleven years later. 2 Kings 25:1-7.</p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-22-20","title":"Proverbs 22:20","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":22,"verseStart":20,"chapterEnd":22,"verseEnd":20},"content":"<p>ter\" subType=\"x-osis2mod\" n=\"$Rev: 3769 $ (SWORD: 1.9.0)\"/></p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-23-intro","title":"Proverbs 23 — Chapter Introduction","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":23,"verseStart":0,"chapterEnd":23,"verseEnd":0},"content":"<p>ter\" subType=\"x-osis2mod\" n=\"$Rev: 3769 $ (SWORD: 1.9.0)\"/></p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-24-16","title":"Proverbs 24:16","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":24,"verseStart":16,"chapterEnd":24,"verseEnd":16},"content":"<p>fear (See Scofield \"Psalms 19:9\") .</p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-24-21","title":"Proverbs 24:21","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":24,"verseStart":21,"chapterEnd":24,"verseEnd":21},"content":"<p>while he (See Scofield \"Jeremiah 37:11\") .</p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-26-22","title":"Proverbs 26:22","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":26,"verseStart":22,"chapterEnd":26,"verseEnd":22},"content":"<p>ninth month i.e. December.</p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-28-3","title":"Proverbs 28:3","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":28,"verseStart":3,"chapterEnd":28,"verseEnd":3},"content":"<p>ter\" subType=\"x-osis2mod\" n=\"$Rev: 3769 $ (SWORD: 1.9.0)\"/></p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-28-8","title":"Proverbs 28:8","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":28,"verseStart":8,"chapterEnd":28,"verseEnd":8},"content":"<p>ter\" subType=\"x-osis2mod\" n=\"$Rev: 3769 $ (SWORD: 1.9.0)\"/></p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-29-4","title":"Proverbs 29:4","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":29,"verseStart":4,"chapterEnd":29,"verseEnd":4},"content":"<p>ter\" subType=\"x-osis2mod\" n=\"$Rev: 3769 $ (SWORD: 1.9.0)\"/></p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-30-16","title":"Proverbs 30:16","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":30,"verseStart":16,"chapterEnd":30,"verseEnd":16},"content":"<p>ter\" subType=\"x-osis2mod\" n=\"$Rev: 3769 $ (SWORD: 1.9.0)\"/></p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-31-7","title":"Proverbs 31:7","author":"C. I. Scofield (1843–1921)","reference":{"book":"PRO","chapterStart":31,"verseStart":7,"chapterEnd":31,"verseEnd":7},"content":"<p>ter\" subType=\"x-osis2mod\" n=\"$Rev: 3769 $ (SWORD: 1.9.0)\"/></p>"},{"id":"scofield-pro-31-27","title":"Proverbs 31:27","autho